no extra dependencies or Docker are needed if we can use a local Vert.x HttpServer. It’s worth noting that the agent_guidance can accommodate local server use as part of the test code setup. I don’t need to repeat any dependency mentions.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "{\n  \"action\": \"advisory_preparation\",\n  \"summary\": \"io.vertx:vertx-web-client:5.0.1 resolves to Vert.x 5.0.1 with Netty 4.2.2.Final; meaningful tests can use the transitive Vert.x core HTTP server locally, but Java 25 native-image runs need the same Netty unsafe-access system properties already used for 5.0.0.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"Do not add external services or extra Maven dependencies. Build coverage around WebClient talking to a local Vert.x HttpServer on 127.0.0.1, covering GET/POST, headers, JSON/body codecs, forms or multipart, redirects/cookies/session/cache as appropriate. Ensure native test execution for the 5.0.x Vert.x/Netty stack sets: -Dsun.misc.unsafe.memory.access=allow and -Dio.netty.tryReflectionSetAccessible=true.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"The existing 5.0.0 scaffold only applies the Netty system properties when libraryVersion == '5.0.0'; the 5.0.1 run can miss them unless the condition is widened or equivalent native runtime args are set.\",\n    \"Multipart/file-stream tests exercise asynchronous Netty/Vert.x paths and can expose native-only timing or access issues; local Gradle/native-image verification remains authoritative.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0252f27a45f99ad7016a422ad1e5308194837cab30cd38b20b\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1333, "output": 819, "cacheRead": 19968, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 22120, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782721221091, "responseId": "resp_0252f27a45f99ad7016a422ac58cfc8194aecf5175a45bf831"}, "to